<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 6. Pseudosubria assamensis sp. nov. A-E female: A habitus lateral view; B head and pronotum; C ovipositor; D, E subgenital plate in ventral (D) and lateral view (E). - F-N male holotype: F left tegmen; G stridulatory file; H base of left tegmen; I mirror of right tegmen; J subgenital plate in lateral view; K, L cercus in external (K) and internal (L) view; M, N phallus with titillators. Abbeviations: 7 seventh sternite, m membrane, ov base of ovipositor, sg lateral lobes of subgenital plate." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/487063" .

